conversation_history.content: i am so sad! my stupid mom wont let me go to the prom after-party. prom night is supposed to be the BEST night of my life, and e me my first kiss!!!

It's understandable to feel sad when something you were looking forward to doesn't go as planned. It seems like you're experiencing "catastrophizing," where you anticipate the worst possible outcome from a situation. Remember, while missing the after-party is disappointing, it doesn't mean your entire prom night or future romantic experiences are ruined. A practical step could be to plan a special event for another day with friends or someone special, creating your own memorable experience.
It looks like you might not have shared what's on your mind yet. If you're feeling down or troubled about something, feel free to share, and I can help you work through those thoughts.
